@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1 class="text-center">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="container mt-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <p class="lead text-muted text-center">Your privacy is important to us. We are committed to protecting your information and being transparent about our data practices.</p>

            <hr />

            <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
            <p>Welcome to BlockOut! We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your data is used responsibly. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our services.</p>

            <h3>2. Information We Collect</h3>
            <p>We collect only the information necessary to provide our services and ensure smooth functionality. This may include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account Information</strong>: When you create an account, we collect your username, email address, and password.</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Data</strong>: We may collect data on how you use our website to improve functionality and user experience.</li>
                <li><strong>Business and Scheduling Data</strong>: Data entered for scheduling and management purposes, such as business names, schedules, and user roles, is stored to ensure your account works as expected.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3. How We Use Your Information</h3>
            <p>We use your data solely for the purpose of providing and improving our services. Specifically, we use it to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Provide access to scheduling and management tools within BlockOut.</li>
                <li>Personalize and enhance your user experience.</li>
                <li>Maintain and improve our services based on usage patterns and feedback.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h3>
            <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for any marketing or advertising purposes. We may share your data only in the following limited circumstances:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Legal Compliance</strong>: We may disclose information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>5. No Ads and No Data Sales</h3>
            <p><strong>At BlockOut, we prioritize user privacy.</strong> We do not run ads on our platform, nor do we sell any user data to third parties. Our platform is ad-free, and your data remains yours.</p>

            <h3>6. Data Retention</h3>
            <p>We retain only the necessary information required for functionality. Any data that is no longer needed for these purposes will be deleted or anonymized.</p>

            <h3>7. Data Security</h3>
            <p>We take the security of your data seriously and implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect it from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.</p>

            <h3>8. Your Data Rights</h3>
            <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data, including the right to access, correct, delete, or limit how we use your data. To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <strong>asvaller@ksu.edu</strong>.</p>

            <h3>9. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h3>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and we will notify you of significant changes where required.</p>

            <h3>10. Contact Us</h3>
            <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please reach out to us at <strong>asvaller@ksu.edu</strong>.</p>

            <hr />
            <p class="text-center text-muted">Thank you for trusting BlockOut with your data.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
